<li id="cite_note-65"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-65">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The Yukon did not join the Flood Damage Reduction Program, and Alberta joined in 1989, a year before the Program began to wind down. James P. Bruce, former Environment Canada assistant deputy minister, notes that Alberta's reluctance to join the Program was understandable given that it would have meant designating all of downtown Calgary as floodplain.<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/story/2013/06/26/f-climate-change-flooding-weather-preparation.html?cmp=rss">CBC</a></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-CUPjan2013Simonovi-66"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-CUPjan2013Simonovi_66-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation book">Slobodan P. Simonović (January 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://scholar.google.ca/citations?user=Vqu6r2EAAAAJ&amp;hl=en"><i>Floods in a Changing Climate: Risk Management</i></a>. International Hydrology Series. Cambridge University Press. p.&#160;194. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781107018747" title="Special:BookSources/9781107018747">9781107018747</a>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+flooding+in+Canada&amp;rft.aulast=Slobodan+P.+Simonovi%C4%87&amp;rft.au=Slobodan+P.+Simonovi%C4%87&amp;rft.btitle=Floods+in+a+Changing+Climate%3A+Risk+Management&amp;rft.date=January+2013&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fscholar.google.ca%2Fcitations%3Fuser%3DVqu6r2EAAAAJ%26hl%3Den&amp;rft.isbn=9781107018747&amp;rft.pages=194&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.series=International+Hydrology+Series&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-67"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-67">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Canadian home owners invest more in "costly basement upgrades" so with floods the cost of rebuild, repair or replacement is much higher than it used to be <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ibc.ca/en/natural_disasters/documents/mcbean_report.pdf">IBC</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-68"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-68">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Although it never reached the level of a flood, on 5 March 2011, in the aftermath of a record rainfall in Ontario and Quebec Crawford &amp; Company claims adjusters 9 March 2011 report entitled in 'Increase in Claims After Heavy Rainfall Hits Parts of Ontario and Quebec' in <i>Canadian Underwriter</i> saw a 300% increase in claims volume for branches and local contractors.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Macrael23jun2013-69"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Macrael23jun2013_69-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation news">Macrael, Kim (23 June 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/federal-government-ready-to-foot-the-bill-for-alberta-flooding-damage/article12762885">"Federal government ready to help foot the bill for Alberta flooding damage"</a>. Ottawa, Ontario: Globe and Mail.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+flooding+in+Canada&amp;rft.aufirst=Kim&amp;rft.aulast=Macrael&amp;rft.au=Macrael%2C+Kim&amp;rft.btitle=Federal+government+ready+to+help+foot+the+bill+for+Alberta+flooding+damage&amp;rft.date=23+June+2013&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Ffederal-government-ready-to-foot-the-bill-for-alberta-flooding-damage%2Farticle12762885&amp;rft.place=Ottawa%2C+Ontario&amp;rft.pub=Globe+and+Mail&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-DFAA2008-70"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-DFAA2008_70-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-DFAA2008_70-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation journal"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.publicsafety.gc.ca/prg/em/dfaa/dfaa-guide-2008-eng.aspx">"Guidelines for the Disaster Financial Assistance Arrangements: for events on or subsequent to January 1, 2008"</a>. Ottawa, Canada: Public Safety Canada. 2008.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+flooding+in+Canada&amp;rft.btitle=Guidelines+for+the+Disaster+Financial+Assistance+Arrangements%3A+for+events+on+or+subsequent+to+January+1%2C+2008&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.publicsafety.gc.ca%2Fprg%2Fem%2Fdfaa%2Fdfaa-guide-2008-eng.aspx&amp;rft.place=Ottawa%2C+Canada&amp;rft.pub=Public+Safety+Canada&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-71"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-71">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation report"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://a100.gov.bc.ca/pub/eirs/finishDownloadDocument.do?subdocumentId=7591">History and Evolution of Stormwater Management: North American Context</a> (Report). BC Government.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+flooding+in+Canada&amp;rft.btitle=History+and+Evolution+of+Stormwater+Management%3A+North+American+Context&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fa100.gov.bc.ca%2Fpub%2Feirs%2FfinishDownloadDocument.do%3FsubdocumentId%3D7591&amp;rft.pub=BC+Government&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Groeneveld10nov2006-72"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Groeneveld10nov2006_72-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Groeneveld10nov2006_72-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation report">George Groeneveld (10 November 2006). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.aema.alberta.ca/images/News/Provincial_Flood_Mitigation_Report.pdf">2006 Provincial Flood Mitigation Report</a> (PDF) (Report). Provincial Flood Mitigation Report Consultation and Recommendation.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+flooding+in+Canada&amp;rft.au=George+Groeneveld&amp;rft.aulast=George+Groeneveld&amp;rft.btitle=2006+Provincial+Flood+Mitigation+Report&amp;rft.date=10+November+2006&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.aema.alberta.ca%2Fimages%2FNews%2FProvincial_Flood_Mitigation_Report.pdf&amp;rft.series=Provincial+Flood+Mitigation+Report+Consultation+and+Recommendation&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-CBC23jun2013-73"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-CBC23jun2013_73-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation news">Gollom, Mark (23 June 2013). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.cbc.ca/news/credit.html">"Alberta flood zone development was a mistake, former MLA says: 2006 flood report called for the end of land sales in known flood risk areas"</a>. CBC News.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+flooding+in+Canada&amp;rft.aufirst=Mark&amp;rft.au=Gollom%2C+Mark&amp;rft.aulast=Gollom&amp;rft.btitle=Alberta+flood+zone+development+was+a+mistake%2C+former+MLA+says%3A+2006+flood+report+called+for+the+end+of+land+sales+in+known+flood+risk+areas&amp;rft.date=23+June+2013&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fcredit.html&amp;rft.pub=CBC+News&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-ExABFloods-74"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-ExABFloods_74-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation report"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.transportation.alberta.ca/Content/doctype30/Production/extfldcont.pdf">Context of Extreme Alberta Floods</a> (PDF) (Report). Alberta Infrastructure and Transportation (INFTRA).</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+flooding+in+Canada&amp;rft.btitle=Context+of+Extreme+Alberta+Floods&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.transportation.alberta.ca%2FContent%2Fdoctype30%2FProduction%2Fextfldcont.pdf&amp;rft.pub=Alberta+Infrastructure+and+Transportation+%28INFTRA%29&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Lorinc2012-75"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Lorinc2012_75-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation news">Lorinc, John (Spring 2012). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.magazine.utoronto.ca/category/spring-2012">"As New Orleans rebuilds, U of T students are helping the city rethink its approach to water management"</a>. <i>U of T:Leading Edge</i>. Flood Control (Toronto, Ontario).</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+flooding+in+Canada&amp;rft.atitle=As+New+Orleans+rebuilds%2C+U+of+T+students+are+helping+the+city+rethink+its+approach+to+water+management&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rft.aulast=Lorinc&amp;rft.au=Lorinc%2C+John&amp;rft.date=Spring+2012&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.magazine.utoronto.ca%2Fcategory%2Fspring-2012&amp;rft.jtitle=U+of+T%3ALeading+Edge&amp;rft.place=Toronto%2C+Ontario&amp;rft.series=Flood+Control&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Delta31jan2013-77"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Delta31jan2013_77-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation journal"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.fcm.ca/Documents/presentations/2013/webinars/Rainwater_Management_Landscape-Based_Solutions_In_Delta_BC_EN.pdf">"Rainwater Management: Landscape-Based Solutions in Delta, BC"</a> (PDF). The Corporation of Delta Green Municipal Fund. 31 January 2013.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+flooding+in+Canada&amp;rft.btitle=Rainwater+Management%3A+Landscape-Based+Solutions+in+Delta%2C+BC&amp;rft.date=31+January+2013&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.fcm.ca%2FDocuments%2Fpresentations%2F2013%2Fwebinars%2FRainwater_Management_Landscape-Based_Solutions_In_Delta_BC_EN.pdf&amp;rft.pub=The+Corporation+of+Delta+Green+Municipal+Fund&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
